Apple Fined by European Commission
----------------------------------

From the Financial Times ( https://www.ft.com/content/05606b16-8c4d-4535-89=
3e-af909fcf22f0 ) :

Brussels has fined Apple more than =E2=82=AC1.8bn for stifling competition =
from rival music streaming services, the first time the iPhone maker has be=
en punished for breaching EU law. Margrethe Vestager, the bloc=E2=80=99s co=
mpetition chief, said the tech giant had broken EU antitrust rules for a de=
cade by =E2=80=9Crestricting developers from informing consumers about alte=
rnative, cheaper music services available outside of the Apple ecosystem=E2=
=80=9D. She said this amounted to abuse of the group=E2=80=99s dominant pos=
ition for music streaming on its App Store=E2=80=A6

The commission said it had gone beyond its standard fining procedure to pro=
vide a deterrent not just for Apple but for other =E2=80=9Ccompanies of a s=
imilar size and with similar resources=E2=80=9D. Vestager said that the =E2=
=80=9Ctraditional part of the fine=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94 around =E2=82=AC40mn =
=E2=80=94 was =E2=80=9Cquite small, not even a speeding ticket, parking tic=
ket=E2=80=9D. As a result, the commission increased the total fine to =E2=
=82=AC1.84bn, which Vestager said amounted to 0.5 per cent of Apple=E2=80=
=99s worldwide turnover.

I wrote briefly about this impending decision back on February 19 ( https:/=
/stratechery.com/2024/xboxs-announcement-microsofts-messy-middle-apple-in-e=
urope-continued/?access_token=3DeyJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiIsImtpZCI6InN0cmF0ZWNoZXJ=
