DPNkFZ-h8_UaCLsR_ZH9o_fSw ) ; it wasn=E2=80=99t some sort of altruistic res=
ponse to developer feedback.
* It is called the =E2=80=9Creader rule=E2=80=9D because it only applies to=
 a limited set of apps which contain magazines, newspapers, books, audio, m=
usic, or video.
* The =E2=80=9Creader rule=E2=80=9D entails applying to Apple for a link en=
titlement for one single link to your website to create or manage your acco=
unt.
* The anti-steering provisions of the App Store still apply, in that you ca=
n=E2=80=99t have any arbitrary link, and you can=E2=80=99t say that you off=
er subscriptions or products for sale, or include any pricing information i=
n your app.

The reader rule is, to be clear, better than nothing; it also, in many resp=
ects, highlights just how absurd the anti-steering provision is. The fact S=
potify can=E2=80=99t even say there are subscriptions for sale, much less g=
ive a price, accomplishes what, exactly? According to Apple, Spotify, by si=
mply telling the user the truth, would be unfairly benefiting from the trus=
t Apple has built with users; how, exactly, is it trust-affirming to demand=
 that developers withhold factual information from those users?

The real kicker for me, though, came in the conclusion:

The digital music market is a great example of the app economy at work. Aft=
er all, over the App Store=E2=80=99s 15 years, a simple phrase =E2=80=94 th=
ere=E2=80=99s an app for that =E2=80=94 has become a universal truth. And t=
oday, behind every app is a wildly successful company or an aspiring entrep=
reneur chasing a dream.

Apple just spent over 1,500 words complaining about how Spotify is acting e=
ntitled by wanting to tell users how to subscribe to their service, which i=
s directly competitive with Apple=E2=80=99s own service, and making it clea=
r that =E2=80=9Cdevelopers owe us=E2=80=9D is not just a legal strategy but=
 Apple=E2=80=99s official corporate policy. To in this context invoke =E2=
=80=9CThere=E2=80=99s an app for that=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94 a phrase that once=
 spoke to the vitality of the developer ecosystem and how developers helped=
 make the iPhone what it is =E2=80=94=C2=A0is to invert the meaning: Apple =
now believes there is an app for that because of Apple. And again, this isn=
=E2=80=99t even wrong, but it=E2=80=99s also not entirely right.

